msgid "Details"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The Tarantool Cartridge framework is deprecated and is not compatible with "
"Tarantool 3.0 and later. This command is added for backward compatibility "
"with earlier versions."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``tt init`` checks the existence of configuration files for Cartridge "
"(``cartridge.yml``) or the ``tarantoolctl`` utility (``.tarantoolctl``) in "
"the current directory. If such files are found, ``tt`` generates an "
"environment that uses the same directories:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``cartridge.yml`` -- the directories specified in the file."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``.tarantoolctl`` -- the directories specified in the ``default_cfg`` table."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``init`` is the only ``tt`` command that invokes ``.tarantoolctl`` files. "
"Thus, variables defined in this script will not be available in applications"
" launched by a ``tt start`` call."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If there is no ``cartridge.yml`` or ``.tarantoolctl`` files in the current "
"directory, ``tt init`` creates a default environment in it. This includes "
"creating the following directories and files:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``bin`` -- the directory for storing binary files."
msgstr ""

msgid "``include`` -- the directory for storing  header files."
msgstr ""

msgid "``distfiles`` -- the directory for storing installation files."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``instances.enabled`` -- the directory for storing running applications or "
"symlinks."
msgstr ""

msgid "``modules`` -- the directory for storing external modules."
msgstr ""

msgid "``tt.yaml`` -- the configuration file."
msgstr ""

msgid "``templates`` -- the directory for storing application templates."
msgstr ""

